Problem: Single Number
Topic: Arrays, Bit Manipulation
Difficulty: Easy
Approach:
Use XOR operation on all elements. Since a ^ a = 0 and a ^ 0 = a, all duplicate numbers cancel out, leaving only the single number.
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int singleNumber(vector<int>& nums) {
       int res=0;
       for(int num: nums){
        res=res^num;  //res^=num
       }
       return res;
    }
};
